public class DateCriterionChoice
extends com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase
implements Versionable, com.guidewire.pl.system.service.search.SearchCriterionChoice
    DateCriterionChoice A component used as part of a larger search criteria entity. Encapsulates the information entered by the user to restrict the search to a particular date range. Specifies the date field to be restricted and allows the date range to be restricted either through a typelist of preset ranges (such as next 30 days) or through a start and end date.

    Very similar to DateCriteria, but DateCriterionChoice supports configurable search. (See the Configuration Guide for details of customizing search screens.)

        public void addToRestriction(com.guidewire.pl.system.database.Restriction restriction,
                             IQueryColumn queryColumn)
        Add clauses to the given restriction, as specified by the current criterion values. Should only be called if isSet() returns true. Usually called automatically by the search configuration framework as part of com.guidewire.pl.system.service.search.config.CriteriaDef#addToRestriction. May also be called manually by custom search criteria code if the search configuration cannot express how the criterion should be applied - for example if joins or sub queries are involved.
